---
description: Frontend rules for the Next.js client
globs:
  - "apps/client/**/*"
alwaysApply: false
---

- Keep components ideally under about 100 lines.
- Keep one React component per file, with the exported component name matching the filename.
- Move secondary UI pieces into their own component files and pure helpers into utilities.
- Split scan result screens into feature components and pure utilities.
- Keep API calls in services/hooks.
- Use typed props and imported API payload types.
- Extract risk formatting, severity styles, and chart mapping from UI components.
- Preserve visual behavior unless a UI change is requested.
